rComments: Hands down one of my favorite courses in my undergrad so far. His passion for the subject shows with his enthusiasm during lecture and his funny and entertaining re-telling of the myths. Although he does review the myths in class, keeping up with the readings (which are fairly brief) makes this course not too difficult.

I literally did not do any reading and did not need to study, just went to the lectures (which were very enjoyable) and got a easy B-, if you spend even an hour a week to review the lectures you would probably get an A

Adam Barker taught me CLA204 at U of T St. George, and he has been one of the funniest, enthusiastic and competent lecturers I've ever had. He never fails to make the class laugh and is always accessible for help for assignments/tests. You should go to lectures as a lot of his material is from lectures/readings, but you won't regret it.

Absolutely amazing professor. He is very passionate about the content he goes over in lecture and makes everything very easy to understand. His story-telling ability was fantastic and that made it very easy to retain the things we went over in lecture.

I think CLA204 is the most exciting course I take this semester, Barker is a super nice guy. He makes me love mythology. I just say I won't regret it if you take his course. I really hope he can stay at UofT after he gets his Ph.D. degree.

Adam is so funny and enthusiastic about classics and mythology. His lectures really help you understand the myths better that you'll have to read and he goes over the important concepts in lecture as well. Keep up with readings so you know which stories he's talking about. I want to emphasize that he is so funny and makes the lectures entertaining.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: GREAT PROF. Was expecting to hate summer school, but he makes going to the classes worth it. Super funny and enthusiastic, explains the myths in a way that sticks in your mind. Readings aren't completely necessary, since he goes over them in class. WOULD TAKE AGAIN!

The most enthusiastic, charismatic, and funniest prof. The lectures are quite heavy; but, he makes them very entertaining for you to remember. The readings are quite long and sometimes confusing and the exams require you to know very minute details in order to do well.

Definitely the best prof Ive had so far. Really passionate about what hes teaching which makes his lectures super enjoyable. Two midterms which were pretty easy and one final project. Readings werent completely necessary since he goes over them in class and what he says WILL stick in your mind.
